cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about a neural model for machine reading comprehension, which involves natural language processing and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper uses reinforcement learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The model also involves attention mechanisms and reasoning, which are common topics in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses a dataset that includes text passages, which could be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as well.
